examples
--------
# adding FOREIGN KEY and UNIQUE constraint
    - let pg auto generate constraint name

    ALTER TABLE products
    ADD FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products ON DELETE SET NULL;

    ALTER TABLE tags 
    ADD UNIQUE (label);

    - explicitly specify constraint name

    ALTER TABLE child_table
    ADD CONSTRAINT parent_id1_id2_fk 
        FOREIGN KEY (parent_id1, parent_id2) 
        REFERENCES parent (id1, id2) ON DELETE CASCADE;

# drop constraint

    ALTER TABLE some_table
    DROP constraint constraint_name

- defining constraint during CREATE TABLE

    CREATE TABLE table_name(
        ...column definition...

        CONSTRAINT constraint_name <constraint_definition>
    )

    <constraint_definition> can be any of:
        CHECk (...)
        UNIQUE (...)
        PRIMARY KEY (...)
        EXCLUDE (...)
        FOREIGN KEY (...)

- removing a constraint

    ALTER table table_name
    DROP CONSTRAINT [IF EXISTS] constraint_name [RESTRICT| CASCADE]

- renaming a constraint

    ALTER table table_name
    RENAME CONSTRAINT constraint_name TO new_constraint_name

- altering constraint

    ALTER table table_name
    ALTER CONSTRAINT constraint_name 
        [DEFERRABLE|NOT DEFERRABLE] [INITIALLY DEFERRED|INITIALLY IMMEDIATE]

- adding a constraint

    ALTER table table_name
    ADD <table_constraint> 

    # where <table_constraint> can be:

    [ CONSTRAINT constraint_name ] # optional constraint name
        {   CHECK ( ... ) |
            UNIQUE index_parameters |
            PRIMARY KEY index_parameters |
            EXCLUDE (...) |
            FOREIGN KEY (column_names...) REFERENCES reftable (refcolumn_names...)
                [MATCH FULL | MATCH PARTIAL | MATCH SIMPLE] 
                [ON DELETE action] 
                [ON UPDATE action]
        }
    [DEFERRABLE | NOT DEFERRABLE] 
    [INITIALLY DEFERRED | INITIALLY IMMEDIATE]
    
- <column_constraint>

    [ CONSTRAINT constraint_name ]
        {   NOT NULL |
            NULL |
            CHECK ( ... ) |
            DEFAULT default_expr |
            GENERATED ... |
            UNIQUE index_parameters |
            PRIMARY KEY index_parameters |
            REFERENCES reftable (...)
        }
    [DEFERRABLE | NOT DEFERRABLE] 
    [INITIALLY DEFERRED | INITIALLY IMMEDIATE]

